{# goal: Compute normalized convergence metric [0,1] from evidence counts only: unresolved runtime threats (0.40), defense-layer runtime coverage verified by firing (0.25), threat-pattern taxonomy coverage (0.15), regression library growth (0.10), residual runtime risk (0.10). Emit cns.runtime.convergence span (P9) ‚Äî namespace registered in CANONICAL_NAMESPACES (event.rs). Replicant_host mandatory (P12). Minimal: evidence-based computation, no synthetic metrics (P5, P8). #}
{# Computes normalized metric [0, 1] where 0 = fully converged #}
{# Emits cns.runtime.convergence CNS span (P9) ‚Äî namespace registered #}

INPUT: unresolved_threats = {{ unresolved_threats }} (from previous cycle or current)
INPUT: defense_layers_firing = {{ defense_layers_firing }} (from emit-regulation/classify-threat)
INPUT: defense_layers_silent = {{ defense_layers_silent }}
INPUT: existing_regressions = {{ existing_regressions }} (count of surface: runtime entries)
INPUT: proposed_regressions = {{ proposed_regressions }} (count from current cycle)
INPUT: previous_metric = {{ previous_metric | default(1.0) }}
INPUT: replicant_host = {{ replicant_host }} (P12)

COMPUTE METRIC (weighted ‚Äî evidence-based only, P8, P5):
- Critical + high unresolved threats weight: 0.40
  Score = 0.00 if zero critical/high; +0.40 if any critical/high remains.
  Partial = (count_critical * 1.0 + count_high * 0.5) / max(1, previous_critical + previous_high) ‚Äî only if evidence-backed.
- Defense-layer firing coverage weight: 0.25
  6 layers firing (input_filtering, output_filtering, canary_detection,
  runtime_policy, regulation_loop, action_distribution_monitoring) = +0.00
  5 firing = +0.04; 4 = +0.08; 3 = +0.13; 2 = +0.19; 1 = +0.25
  Each layer only counts as firing when actual `cns.guard.*` or
  `cns.regulation.*` span emissions confirm it (P8 ‚Äî concrete evidence
  only, no aspirational coverage). Distinct from kali-audit's static
  presence check ‚Äî this measures runtime firing, not code presence.
- Threat-pattern taxonomy coverage weight: 0.15
  All 4 threat types (endpoint_abuse, bot_traffic, llm_usage_spipe,
  dependency_behavior_anomaly) covered by at least one finding/proposed
  regression = +0.00
  3 covered = +0.04; 2 = +0.08; 1 = +0.12; 0 = +0.15
- Regression library growth weight: 0.10
  New `surface: runtime` regression proposed this cycle = +0.00
  No new proposal despite evidence = +0.10 (stagnation)
  Existing `enforced` regressions remain enforced (no regression removal in metric).
- Residual runtime risk weight: 0.10
  Zero unresolved runtime anomalies in observation window = +0.00
  Any remaining critical/high runtime threat = +0.10

SUM = sum of contributions, clamp [0, 1].

CONVERGENCE CHECK (P9 ‚Äî homeostatic regulation):
- Metric ‚â§ 0.10: near converged.
- Metric ‚â§ 0.10 AND relative improvement ‚â• 5% from previous_metric: converged.
- If metric > 0.10 OR improvement < 5%: not converged ‚Äî identify blockers.
- Blockers = specific defense-layer firing gaps (from `defense_layers_silent`),
  unresolved critical/high threats (with span evidence), stagnation
  (no new regression proposed despite threat evidence), taxonomy gaps
  (threat types uncovered by findings/proposals).

CNS SPAN (P9):
- `cns.runtime.convergence` is registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit span unconditionally:
  (`target: "cns.runtime.convergence"`, message: `"CNS"`,
  operation: `"convergence_check"`, metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct,
  blockers: [...], replicant_host, latency_ms).

OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON):
`{convergence_metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct, converged: bool,
blockers: [...], defense_layers_firing, defense_layers_silent,
existing_regressions_count, proposed_regressions_count, unresolved_critical,
unresolved_high, taxonomy_coverage, residual_runtime_risk, replicant_host,
cns_span_emitted: true}`.

5W1H GATE (P5 ‚Äî minimal): Who = replicant host; What = convergence metric;
Where = deployed runtime environment / observation window; When = monitoring
cycle; Why = P9 observable self-correction / P7 evolutionary progress;
How = compute metric + check improvement + emit CNS span + identify blockers.
All 6 present.

